<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-129-514  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 129 514.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Feb 5 1990 n576 p22(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Super export rules to relax? (supercomputers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Department of Commerce is planning to increase thethreshold at which computers are subject to export control tosupercomputers capable of 300 Mflops.andP;  The proposed regulationswould apply to the 17 member CoCom countries and to seven otherwestern nations.andP;  The regulations allow supercomputers capable offrom 150 to 300 Mflops to be exported to these countries with onlyminimal safeguards.andP;  Computers capable of less than 150 Mflops canbe exported to other non-communist countries.andP;  Under the proposedrules certain mini-supercomputers and workstations would becomeexempt from regulation.andP;  The Department of Defense predictablyopposes any relaxation of the regulations, while industry forceswere pushing for a threshold as high as 600 Mflops.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of CommerceExportInternational TradeSupercomputersGovernment Regulation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>